but I hope my thinking here gives some flavor of what kinds of things
I'm thinking about.</p>

<h2><a href="#writing" id="writing">Writing</a></h2>
<p>I'm more and more realizing the value of being able to write well,
as a software engineer &amp; in general, and have not been doing
enough of it myself &mdash; especially in public.</p>

<p>I am a huge fan of Gwern Branwen's writings &amp; his philosophy
here, especially this bit (my emphasis):</p>
<ul><li>&ldquo;Half the challenge of fighting procrastination
is the pain of starting &mdash; I find when I actually get into the swing of
working on even dull tasks, it’s not so bad. So this suggests a
solution: never start. Merely have <strong>perpetual drafts</strong>, which one tweaks
from time to time. And the rest takes care of itself.&rdquo;<sup><a href="http://www.gwern.net/About"
target="_blank">1</a></sup></li></ul>

<p>I hope that my background and perspectives can be useful to some of
you, and that I can produce perpetual drafts on some topics of
interest.</p>

<p>I also think that my writing can serve purposes to myself as well,
revealing my thinking on topics at various times in the past &mdash;
hopefully I'll be able to eventually look back, cringe, and continue
&ldquo;making better mistakes tomorrow&rdquo;.</p>

